# Prompt 026: Tag Enhancements - Colors, Smart Suggestions, Bulk Operations (P2)

## Objective
Add tag color customization, smart tag suggestions based on content, and bulk tag operations to complete professional tag management parity with Bear/Notion.

## Context
- **Feature:** Notes & Knowledge Management (P2 - Tag enhancements)
- **Current State:** Hierarchical tagging, inline tags, tag manager, tag filters all functional
- **Gaps:**
  1. No custom colors for tags (visual organization)
  2. No smart tag suggestions based on note content
  3. No bulk tag operations (add/remove tags from multiple notes)
- **Priority:** P2 - Convenience features, not critical for core organization

## Requirements

### Part 1: Tag Colors

#### 1.1 Color Picker in Tag Manager
**Purpose:** Assign custom colors to tags for visual organization

**Implementation:**
```typescript
// In src/types/notes.ts
export interface Tag {
  name: string;
  count: number;
  color?: string; // NEW: hex color (e.g., "#3b82f6")
  lastUsed?: string; // ISO date
}

// In src/components/TagManager.tsx
import { HexColorPicker } from 'react-colorful';

const [editingColor, setEditingColor] = useState<string | null>(null);

// For each tag in manager:
<button
  onClick={() => setEditingColor(tag.name)}
  className="w-6 h-6 rounded-full border-2"
  style={{ backgroundColor: tag.color || '#64748b' }}
  aria-label="Change tag color"
/>

{editingColor === tag.name && (
  <Popover>
    <HexColorPicker
      color={tag.color || '#64748b'}
      onChange={(newColor) => updateTagColor(tag.name, newColor)}
    />
    <button onClick={() => setEditingColor(null)}>Done</button>
  </Popover>
)}
```

**Dependencies:**
```bash
npm install react-colorful
```

#### 1.2 Color Display in Tags
**Purpose:** Show custom colors in all tag displays

**Implementation:**
```typescript
// In src/components/TagPicker.tsx
<span
  className="px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs"
  style={{
    backgroundColor: `${tag.color || '#64748b'}20`, // 20 = 12% opacity
    color: tag.color || '#64748b',
    borderColor: tag.color || '#64748b',
  }}
>
  {tag.name}
</span>

// In Notes list view:
{note.tags.map(tagName => {
  const tagColor = getTagColor(tagName); // Look up in store
  return (
    <span
      key={tagName}
      style={{
        backgroundColor: `${tagColor}20`,
        color: tagColor,
        borderColor: tagColor,
      }}
      className="px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs border"
    >
      {tagName}
    </span>
  );
})}
```

